    # [LCModel.f:3747] c           ------------------------------------------------------------------
    # [LCModel.f:3748] c           Choose NDATA_FREQ so that bw_basis_new = bw_data.
    # [LCModel.f:3749] c           If HZPPPM_BASIS is available, then the bandwidth will be adjusted
    # [LCModel.f:3750] c             to compensate for the difference between HZPPPM & HZPPPM_BASIS.
    # [LCModel.f:3751] c           The following reasoning is used:
    # [LCModel.f:3752] c           The basis spectra must be adjusted so that 2 conditions are
    # [LCModel.f:3753] c             matched:
    # [LCModel.f:3754] c             (1) Basis bandwidth must be changed to data bandwidth.
    # [LCModel.f:3755] c                 This is done by truncating or zero-filling the basis
    # [LCModel.f:3756] c                   spectra.  The spacing of the basis spectra remains fixed
    # [LCModel.f:3757] c                   in this step at 1/(ndatab*badelt*hzpppm_basis).
    # [LCModel.f:3758] c                 RNDATA_FREQ = the number of points in DATAT such that the
    # [LCModel.f:3759] c                               total time range of DATAT equals that of
    # [LCModel.f:3760] c                               BASIST; i.e., such that DATAF has the same
    # [LCModel.f:3761] c                               spacing as BASISF
    # [LCModel.f:3762] c                             = NDATAB*BADELT*HZPPPM_BASIS/(DELTAT*HZPPPM)
    # [LCModel.f:3763] c                 Zero-filling or truncating BASISF to NDATA_FREQ points and
    # [LCModel.f:3764] c                   doing an FFTINV produces a BASIST with the same spacing as
    # [LCModel.f:3765] c                   DATAT.  This part is independent of NDATA.
    # [LCModel.f:3766] c             (2) Basis frequency spacing must be changed to data spacing.
    # [LCModel.f:3767] c                   BASIST is zero-filled or truncated to NDATA points, so
    # [LCModel.f:3768] c                   that BASISF matches the spacing of DATAF (as calculated in
    # [LCModel.f:3769] c                   Step (1)).
    # [LCModel.f:3770] c                 This could cause significant errors due to inconsistencies
    # [LCModel.f:3771] c                   in the scaling of the basis spectra caused by (differing
    # [LCModel.f:3772] c                   effects of truncation).  There should be a warning to be
    # [LCModel.f:3773] c                   consistent with NUNFIL*DELTAT with all in vivo data.  In
    # [LCModel.f:3774] c                   practice, could partially reduce this effect with FWHMSM
    # [LCModel.f:3775] c                   in MakeBasis, especially if AUTOSC=T, but it is nice to
    # [LCModel.f:3776] c                   have sharp basis spectra, with plenty of possibility of
    # [LCModel.f:3777] c                   lineshape convolution to correct for lineshape.
    # [LCModel.f:3778] c           ------------------------------------------------------------------
