    # [LCModel.f:14571] C
    # [LCModel.f:14572] C     GIVEN AN M BY N MATRIX, A, AND AN M-VECTOR, B,  COMPUTE AN
    # [LCModel.f:14573] C     N-VECTOR, X, WHICH SOLVES THE LEAST SQUARES PROBLEM
    # [LCModel.f:14574] C
    # [LCModel.f:14575] C                      A * X = B  SUBJECT TO X .GE. 0
    # [LCModel.f:14576] C
    # [LCModel.f:14577] C     A(),MDA,M,N     MDA IS THE FIRST DIMENSIONING PARAMETER FOR THE
    # [LCModel.f:14578] C                     ARRAY, A().   ON ENTRY A() CONTAINS THE M BY N
    # [LCModel.f:14579] C                     MATRIX, A.           ON EXIT A() CONTAINS
    # [LCModel.f:14580] C                     THE PRODUCT MATRIX, Q*A , WHERE Q IS AN
    # [LCModel.f:14581] C                     M BY M ORTHOGONAL MATRIX GENERATED IMPLICITLY BY
    # [LCModel.f:14582] C                     THIS SUBROUTINE.
    # [LCModel.f:14583] C     B()     ON ENTRY B() CONTAINS THE M-VECTOR, B.   ON EXIT B() CON-
    # [LCModel.f:14584] C             TAINS Q*B.
    # [LCModel.f:14585] C     X()     ON ENTRY X() NEED NOT BE INITIALIZED.  ON EXIT X() WILL
    # [LCModel.f:14586] C             CONTAIN THE SOLUTION VECTOR.
    # [LCModel.f:14587] C     DVAR    ON EXIT DVAR CONTAINS THE squared EUCLIDEAN NORM OF THE
    # [LCModel.f:14588] C             RESIDUAL VECTOR.  DVAR is DOUBLE PRECISION.
